      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that's the thing... it's not a winter. seasons change. this is permanent. there's no \"rebuilding\" what isn't there. if you have a house but the foundation is gone, you're just standing in a pile of debris. it feels like the only honest thing left to do is acknowledge that the thing that made life worth living is gone, and there's nothing left to maintain the facade.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
